en_7295259_0	Colombo (News1st): The Speaker’s media unit stated that the seat reserved for the Prime Minister will be allocated for Mahinda Rajapaksa when the Parliament convenes on the 05th of October.
en_7295259_1	It was noted that this is due to the gazette notification issued claiming Mahinda Rajapaksa as the Prime Minister.
en_7295259_2	All state employees are bound to comply with the latest gazette notification.
en_7295259_3	Therefore, the  Speaker’s media unit said the government officials have implemented measures to facilitate this process.
en_7295259_4	The Speaker has further clarified that he will not intervene in the process of state officials providing the entitled facilities to the Prime Minister.
